  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does a fractional CMO cost per month?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Fractional CMO costs typically range from $3,000 to $20,000 per month depending on scope, hours committed, and experience level. Most B2B companies in the $5M–$50M range land between $6,000 and $12,000 per month for a meaningful engagement."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What hourly rate does a fractional CMO charge?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Fractional CMO hourly rates range from $150 to $400 per hour. Most don't work on a pure hourly basis — they package a set number of hours per week into a monthly retainer for predictability on both sides."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do fractional CMOs take equity?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Some do, most don't. Equity arrangements are more common at early-stage startups where cash is tight. For companies doing $5M+, most fractional CMOs prefer all-cash arrangements. If equity is offered, typical grants range from 0.1% to 0.5% vesting over 2–4 years."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is a fractional CMO worth the cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For most B2B companies between $5M and $50M, yes — if the alternative is either no marketing leadership or a full-time hire. A $10,000/month fractional CMO driving 20% pipeline improvement on a $5M ARR business pays back in weeks. The ROI math is usually obvious when you run it."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long do fractional CMO contracts last?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most fractional CMO engagements start with a 3-month pilot, then move to rolling monthly retainers. Average engagement length is 12–18 months. Companies that hire full-time marketing leadership eventually graduate out — which is the point."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>
